# Git Discipline

## Commit policy

- **Commit locally** when a phase completes and validation passes
- Include all relevant changed files in one coherent commit per phase
- Use clear commit messages focused on **why**, not just what

## Before push (mandatory when user requests push)

Any push that includes changes under `web/` **must** pass local CI parity first:

```bash
npm run ci:check --prefix web
```

Run from **repository root** (same as `.github/workflows/ci.yml`). Exit code must be **0** before `git push`.

| Check | Why |
|-------|-----|
| `npm run ci:check --prefix web` | Matches GitHub `lint-and-build` job exactly |
| `ReadLints` on touched files | Catches IDE-only issues before ESLint in CI |

**Never push** after only `typecheck` or partial lint — ESLint rules (e.g. `react-hooks/set-state-in-effect`) fail CI in ~1 minute.

### Remote CI verification (after push)

- Command: `/pre-push-check` for full protocol
- Windows `gh` path when not on PATH: `C:\Program Files\GitHub CLI\gh.exe`
- Requires one-time `gh auth login` in the user terminal; without auth, check GitHub Actions in the browser
- Do not claim "CI green" without run evidence on the pushed SHA

## Never without explicit user request

- `git push` (any remote)
- `git merge`
- Force push (`--force`, `--force-with-lease`)
- Opening PRs (use user rule workflow when requested)
- `git commit --amend` except when user rule conditions are fully met

## Never

- `git push --force` to `main` or `master` — warn user if requested
- `--no-verify`, `--no-gpg-sign`, or other hook bypass unless user explicitly requests
- Updating git config

## When to commit

| Work type | Commit timing |
|-----------|---------------|
| SaaS (`web/`) | After phase validation + ledger update |
| HTML/Next templates | After phase-end gate pass |
| Agent system changes | After compatibility validation |
| Docs-only sync | After doc matches implementation |

## Monorepo routing

When touching multiple roots (`web/`, `sites/`, `Frontend_Nextjs/`), confirm write target before commit. Defer ambiguous topology to git workspace manager patterns in `VSCODE AGENTS/Testing-Cursor_dev/.github/git-workspace-manager/`.

## Evidence in ledger

Record commit hash in session log / tasks ledger after successful local commit.
